ce:section.ce:para:
Understanding internal battery dynamics, in particular, the charge transport mechanisms in porous electrodes, is fundamental for building better batteries. Within lithium-ion battery (LIB) and sodium-ion battery (SIB) electrodes, solid-state diffusion is usually the slowest and thus the rate-determining process. Knowledge of the solid-state diffusion coefficient (
D 1
) and kinetic rate constant
( k
) is therefore fundamental in designing battery electrodes for optimized power and energy efficiency. As a result, it is important to develop experimentally accurate and validated characterization methods, to determine solid-state mass transport parameters.
